"v. 做手势表达 【英】 v. 做手势表达(to make or use gestures) 【记】 来自geste(手势，行 为)，geste+iculate( 产生…的)→产生手势 的→做手势; 【同】 参考：gesture(手势 ，姿态) 【例】 John gesticulated wildly as his speech became more emotional. 无 【记】gesture姿势 + ate gesticulate (v.)  c.1600, from Latin gesticulatus, past participle of gesticulari ""to gesture, mimic,"" from gesticulus ""a mimicking gesture,"" diminutive of gestus ""gesture, carriage, posture"" (see gest). Related: Gesticulated; gesticulating."
